This small loan request is made by five modest women living in Siem Reap Province, Cambodia. Sok H., 53, has been selected as group leader by the other members. She and her husband are good parents who are blessed with four children; two are married and have already started new families, while the other two are single and attend school. 
<p>
The family earns their daily income by fishing in and around the Tunle Sap River and selling their catch at the local market. They have been fishing for more than 19 years and earn around $4 per day to meet their family’s needs. To grow the business and earn additional income, Sok H. is applying for a loan from Kiva’s partner, HKL. She will use this loan to purchase fishing equipment to help them catch more fish. 
<p>
The other four borrowers are:
- V., who will use the loan to repair her old fishing boat;
- S., who also requests a loan to repair her fishing boat;
- K., who is applying for a loan to add to her savings for building a house;
- P., who will use the money to repair her broken fishing boat.
